description:
easy-to-grow beets do double-duty in the kitchen, producing tasty roots
for baking, boiling or sautéing and fresh greens to boil or steam.
plant them early for top quality and best flavor. (fluctuating weather
can reduce quality and create white zone rings in the roots.) some
varieties have red stems and venation in the leaves, making them a
natural for edible landscaping.

than lettuce, frilly-leaved endive makes an attractive addition to

salads, but hot weather makes this cool-season crop bitter and
inedible.
